article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 73, Northwestern St. 45
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Matt Kingsley scored 25 points and grabbed seven rebounds to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 73-45 victory over Northwestern State on Wednesday night. Kingsley made 12-of-15 field goals in the game and was 1-for-1 from the free throw line. Benson Akpan scored 12 points off the bench and Eddie Williams added 11 for the Lumberjacks (13-5, 5-1 Southland). No player was able to reach double digits for Northwestern State (8-12, 0-5). The Demons fell behind 35-26 in the first half then followed that up with a 19-point second half effort in which they made only seven field goals.
